						<div class="postbody">Looks like Cydrak may have found it =^-^=<br /><br />The game is turning LCDC off at LY=148 ($00), then turning it back on again 44 scanlines later ($e7).<br /><br />So the trick is probably that I am still internally hard-driven around a 60fps loop of cycles and don't actually stop all PPU rendering when LY is turned off.<br /><br />I'll have to do some reworking to get this going with higan, but I have a good idea of how to proceed. I'll post again once I have it implemented, and see if it works.<br /><br />Thank you for the input, Shonumi! :D<br /><br />Side note: seems Mednafen is likely wrong to have an orange screen during this part. Should be white as in when LCDC is off.</div>

